# Allowlist for `claude` CLI invocations inside synced shell scripts.
#
# Each entry pins the bytes of one `# claude-cli-invocations:start` /
# `:end` region. The lint at `.claude/lint-claude-cli-invocations.py`
# computes the sha256 of the bytes between each marker pair and refuses
# to pass if the hash isn't listed here — so any change to the locked
# region must also update this file, and the resulting diff is the
# audit trail for the reviewer.
#
# Format (whitespace-separated):
#   <sha256>  <path>:<start_line>  <description>
#
# The line-number field is informational (it tracks the start-marker
# line as of the last edit, so the reviewer can locate the region
# quickly) and is NOT checked by the lint — only the hash is. That
# means whitespace/comment edits *outside* the region don't churn the
# allowlist even if they shift the region's line number.

7e11c4ed3459e678fb187a61c60a43f48d94283a740c699cb3cc7fb40a016b5c  .claude/skills/agent-loop/scripts/agent-loop.sh:471  agent-loop: spawn claude with bypassPermissions + consumer-owned prompt
